data.name: Truffle Mac and Cheese with Crispy Prosciutto
data.quickTastyDescription: A luxurious twist on the classic comfort food, featuring creamy truffle-infused cheese sauce and crispy prosciutto for an exquisite texture and flavor.
detailedCookingInstructions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil and cook the elbow macaroni until al dente, according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Stir in the flour and whisk continuously for about 2 minutes to form a roux.
Gradually add the heavy cream, whisking until smooth and thickened. Stir in the cheddar and Gruyère cheese until melted and creamy.
Add truffle oil, salt, and pepper, adjusting to taste. Combine the cooked macaroni with the cheese sauce until fully coated.
In a separate pan, cook the prosciutto slices over medium heat until crispy. Remove and let drain on paper towels.
Transfer the mac and cheese to a greased baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake for about 20 minutes until golden and bubbling.
Remove from the oven and top with crispy prosciutto and garnish with fresh parsley before serving.
data.detailedName: Truffle Mac and Cheese with Crispy Prosciutto
data.modifiersForBase: Truffle oil and crispy prosciutto for added luxury.
